    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>[Asking for additional details of an edition of <hi rend="underline">Confessions of a Metaphysician</hi> by Count Mariani of Florence<ref target="#foot.f2"/>, which he can read] if it were in French […] but German is too hard work for me without confusion. […] you must have the kindness to inform me, if I do <hi rend="doubleUnderline">not</hi> hear I shall understand that it is, as far as you know, in German or Italian</p>
<p>With my best thanks I remain Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is given in the Kotte sale catalogue, and the year is confirmed by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5059.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Rudolf Suchsland, 16 April 1866</ref> (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In his letter of 16 April 1866 (<hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol 14), Suchsland had mentioned that the second volume of <hi rend="italic">Confessioni di un metafisico</hi> by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_6272.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Terenzio Mamiani della Rovere</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5180.xml" resp="#automat" cert="low">Mamiani della Rovere 1865</ref>) dealt with CD’s theory.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The original letter is complete and is described by Kotte Autographs as being three pages long.</note>
        </div>        
            
